# Backend API development (organization template)

> Document **router layout**, **validation library** (e.g. Zod from codegen), and **response envelope** in **`AGENTS.md`**.

## Contracts

- **Do not** change path, query, or body shapes without updating the API spec (if used) and regenerating types.
- Validate **params, body, and responses** with the same schemas the client expects.

## Errors

- Use HTTP status codes appropriate to the project standard.
- Return the project’s standard error JSON shape (see AGENTS.md).

## Structure

- Prefer **one router module per domain**; mount from a central routes index.
- Keep handlers thin: validate → call service/DB → map to response.

## Security

- Do not log secrets; validate auth on protected routes per project middleware.
